sub_title: Junior Pricing Actuary (Actuaris) at De Goudse Verzekeringen
summary:
Currently working as an actuary at a medical liability insurer (non-life) and studying the Executive Masters of Actuarial Sciences (EMAS) at the Actuarial Institute. 

My main interest is translating financial phenomena and dynamics into mathematical models.  My further studies in the Netherlands has allowed me to directly come in contact with and absorb the latest research within financial modelling. Furthermore, I am actively in my spare time reading the latest research within the field of finance and its interdisciplinary subjects.

My master thesis topic was "Applications of Machine Learning Techniques for Forecasting Exchange Rate Returns in Emerging Economies" with Bart Bos (Cardano) and Anne Balter (Tilburg university) as my supervisors, completed in August 2020. Featured on the Netspar website.

Feel free to contact me if you have any questions, the easiest way to reach me is by sending an email to ms.shahnazari@hotmail.com.
